<collectingRegion box="[722,836,1976,2002]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
include Ubatuba (
<bibRefCitation author="D'Incao, F. &amp; Martins, S. T. S." box="[1045,1332,1976,2002]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="78 - 86" refId="ref60083" refString="D'Incao, F. &amp; Martins, S. T. S. (2000) Brazilian species of the genera Acetes H. Milne Edwards, 1830 and Peisos Burkenroad, 1945 (Decapoda: Sergestidae). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 20 (2), 78 - 86. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1937240 X- 90000010" type="journal article" year="2000">D’Incao &amp; Martins 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, R. C. &amp; Fransozo, A. &amp; Melo, G. A. S. &amp; Freire, F. A. M." pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref59488" refString="Costa, R. C., Fransozo, A., Melo, G. A. S. &amp; Freire, F. A. M. (2003) Chave ilustrada para identificacao dos camaroes Dendrobranchiata do litoral norte do estado de Sao Paulo, Brasil. Biota Neotropica, 3 (1), 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1676 - 06032003000100011" type="journal article" year="2003">
Costa 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
; Simões 
<emphasis box="[349,405,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
2012; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[484,738,2012,2038]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis box="[613,670,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
); it is usually captured in low temperatures (&lt;20 °C) (
<bibRefCitation author="Simoes, S. M. &amp; Castilho, A. L. &amp; Fransozo, A. &amp; Negreiros-Fransozo, M. L. &amp; Costa, R. C." lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="753 - 759" refId="ref78664" refString="Simoes, S. M., Castilho, A. L., Fransozo, A., Negreiros-Fransozo, M. L. &amp; Costa, R. C. (2013) Distribution related to temperature and salinity of the shrimps Acetes americanus and Peisos petrunkevitchi (Crustacea: Sergestoidea) in the south-eastern Brazilian littoral zone. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 93 (3), 753 - 759. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315412000902" type="journal article" year="2013">
Simões 
<emphasis box="[151,208,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Although it may be captured incidentally as bycatch of some commercial shrimps, this species is not considered as endangered or under threats (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, R. C. &amp; Simoes, S. M." box="[627,874,187,214]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="366 - 376" refId="ref59408" refString="Costa, R. C. &amp; Simoes, S. M. (2016) Avaliacao dos camaroes sicionideos (Decapoda: Sicyoniidae). Chapter 27, 366 - 376. In: Pinheiro, M. A. A. &amp; Boos, H. (Org.), Livro Vermelho dos Crustaceos do Brasil: Avaliacao 2010 - 2014. Porto Alegre, RS, Sociedade Brasileira de Carcinologia - SBC, 466 pp." type="book chapter" year="2016">Costa &amp; Simões 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burkenroad" authorityYear="1945" box="[1135,1208,187,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Peisos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1135,1208,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Peisos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had its phylogenetic status tested in relation to other sergestids genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Borradaile, 1910" authorityName="Borradaile" authorityYear="1910" box="[696,1005,223,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Sicyonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[696,813,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sicyonella</emphasis>
Borradaile, 1910
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vereshchaka et al. 2016 a)" baseAuthorityName="Vereshchaka" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1056,1433,223,250]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1129,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Acetes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vereshchaka, A. L. &amp; Lunina, A. A. &amp; Olesen, J." box="[1142,1425,223,250]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="353 - 377" refId="ref81742" refString="Vereshchaka, A. L., Lunina, A. A. &amp; Olesen, J. (2016 a) Phylogeny and classification of the shrimp genera Acetes, Peisos, and Sicyonella (Sergestidae: Crustacea: Decapoda). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 177, 353 - 377. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12371" type="journal article" year="2016">
Vereshchaka 
<emphasis box="[1291,1346,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. These authors combined all species of 
<taxonomicName box="[589,662,259,285]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[589,662,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Acetes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burkenroad" authorityYear="1945" box="[717,905,259,285]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Peisos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrunkevitchi">
<emphasis box="[717,905,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. petrunkevitchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into a single monophyletic genus and consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burkenroad" authorityYear="1945" box="[151,224,295,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Peisos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,224,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Peisos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vereshchaka et al. 2016 a)" baseAuthorityName="Vereshchaka" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[500,885,295,322]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[500,573,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Acetes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vereshchaka, A. L. &amp; Lunina, A. A. &amp; Olesen, J." box="[588,877,295,322]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="353 - 377" refId="ref81742" refString="Vereshchaka, A. L., Lunina, A. A. &amp; Olesen, J. (2016 a) Phylogeny and classification of the shrimp genera Acetes, Peisos, and Sicyonella (Sergestidae: Crustacea: Decapoda). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 177, 353 - 377. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12371" type="journal article" year="2016">
Vereshchaka 
<emphasis box="[739,796,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burkenroad" authorityYear="1945" box="[896,1137,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Peisos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrunkevitchi">
<emphasis box="[896,1137,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Peisos petrunkevitchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<emphasis box="[1203,1395,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
A. a. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ortmann" authorityYear="1893" box="[1264,1395,295,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">americanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
are sympatric species in southeastern and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[677,748,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, which has led to mistaken identifications on previous records (
<bibRefCitation author="D'Incao, F. &amp; Martins, S. T. S." box="[159,447,367,393]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="78 - 86" refId="ref60083" refString="D'Incao, F. &amp; Martins, S. T. S. (2000) Brazilian species of the genera Acetes H. Milne Edwards, 1830 and Peisos Burkenroad, 1945 (Decapoda: Sergestidae). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 20 (2), 78 - 86. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1937240 X- 90000010" type="journal article" year="2000">D’Incao &amp; Martins 2000</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burkenroad" authorityYear="1945" box="[587,828,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Peisos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrunkevitchi">
<emphasis box="[587,828,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Peisos petrunkevitchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still accepted (WoRMS 2022), and considering the non-consolidated opinion among carcinologists and to avoid taxonomic instability, we maintained nomenclature here until there is a consolidated taxonomic treatment of the genus. Sequences accession number (GenBank): CCDB 4940—16S (
<accessionNumber box="[295,424,474,501]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KX196598" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">KX196598</accessionNumber>
), COI (
<accessionNumber box="[507,634,474,501]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KX196540" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">KX196540</accessionNumber>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[656,910,475,501]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis box="[786,842,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
